;***************************************************************************************************

@NODE introduction "Introduction"
@{B}Introduction@{UB}

MiniMail is the result of a few months of pretty hard work. Despite being good, it still isn't even a fraction of what I want it to be. This is mainly because of a fixed deadline, set as a result of doing MiniMail as a "special project" (specialarbete) at school.

MiniMail is simply an integrated email system - it lets you read and write email, without the fuzz of having to rely on external mailers, pop-clients, etc. It was designed to be very user friendly, letting you concentrate on reading and writing your email rather than fuzzing around with a fancy but slow and complex product.

@{" Features " link features}
@ENDNODE

;***************************************************************************************************

@NODE features "Features"
@{B}Features@{UB}

· Quick, smooth, and easy to use. No superfluous GUI engine, like MUI, is used.

· Quick @{" installation " link installation} (and deinstallation).

· Lets you read and write mail both online and offline.

· Built-in POP3 and SMTP clients (for getting and sending mail).

· Capability to automatically check for new mail at regular intervals.

· Support for an alias list (user database), with groups.

· Lets you send mail to many recipients at the same time.

· Reads and understands complex MIME messages (file attachments, ...).

· Iconification via Commodity, and an optional AppIcon/AppMenuItem.

· @{" Locale " link locale} support (for both languages and timezones).

· Complies with most related RFCs (for example 821, 822, 1521 and 1725).

· More...

@{" Installation " link installation}
@ENDNODE

;***************************************************************************************************

@NODE installation "Installation"
@{B}Installation@{UB}

The installation process is very simple - just move or copy the MiniMail drawer to where you want it. From the Workbench, you can simply drag the drawer somewhere onto your harddrive. No permanent files will be created outside MiniMail's drawer, which greatly simplifies deinstallation (just delete the drawer).


@{B}Minimum requirements@{UB}

- AmigaOS release 2.0 (3.0 or better is recommended)

- An installed copy of AmiTCP version 3 or better (not included)

- reqtools.library version 38 or better (not included)

@{" Usage " link usage}
@ENDNODE

